-- Brazil Raises Pensions That Exceed Minimum Wage by 6.08%
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 2012-01-09T13:22:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/brazil-raises-pensions-that-exceed-minimum-wage-by-6-08-.html
Brazil  raised all pensions that
exceed the monthly minimum wage of 622 reais ($337) by 6.08
percent, according to a report published today in the  Official
Gazette .  The 2012 increase, which is equal to 2011 inflation as
measured by the INPC index, applies from Jan. 1, the report
said.  Those receiving the minimum payment received an increase of
14.1 percent, the government said in December.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
